.TH RMPD 1 "July 2026" "rmpd 0.5.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
rmpd \- Rust Music Player Daemon
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B rmpd
[\fB\-c\fR \fICONFIG\fR]
[\fB\-b\fR \fIADDRESS\fR]
[\fB\-p\fR \fIPORT\fR]
[\fB\-v\fR]
[\fB\-d\fR]
[\fB\-\-syslog\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B rmpd
is a modern Music Player Daemon implementation written in Rust.
It provides an MPD-compatible control protocol, local library indexing,
multiple audio output backends, and optional desktop integration through MPRIS.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-c , " " \-\-config "=" \fICONFIG\fR
Load configuration from the given TOML file.
.TP
.BR \-b , " " \-\-bind "=" \fIADDRESS\fR
Bind the MPD TCP listener to the given IPv4 or IPv6 address.
.TP
.BR \-p , " " \-\-port "=" \fIPORT\fR
Listen on the given TCP port.
.TP
.BR \-v , " " \-\-verbose
Enable verbose debug logging.
.TP
.BR \-d , " " \-\-daemonize
Detach into the background after startup.
.TP
.B \-\-syslog
Log to journald/syslog instead of standard output.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/rmpd/rmpd.toml
System-wide configuration file installed by the Debian package.
.TP
.I ~/.config/rmpd/rmpd.toml
Per-user configuration file.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR mpc (1),
.BR ncmpcpp (1)
.SH HOMEPAGE
https://github.com/M0Rf30/rmpd